Image Preprocessing¶

In [6]:
def load_and_preprocess_images(sampled_data, img_size=(224,224), sample_size=5000):  #Defining a function to load and preprocess images
    images= [] #Initialize list to hold images , labels and problematic image indices
    labels= [] 
    problematic_indices= []
    
    
    for index,row in sampled_data.iterrows():
        img_path=os.path.join('D:\photos',f"{row['photo_id']}.jpg")
        try:
            img= load_img(img_path, target_size=img_size) #Loading and resizing the image
            img_array = img_to_array(img) / 255.0 #Converting to array and normalising 
            images.append(img_array) #Appending to images list
            labels.append(row['label']) #Appending to labels list
        except Exception as e:
            print(f"Error loading image {img_path}: {e}")
            problematic_indices.append(index) #Storing index of error occuring images
            
    images_array=np.array(images) #Converting list to array
    labels_array=np.array(labels)
    
    print(f"Total number of images loaded successfully: {len(images_array)}") #Printing the total images loaded
    
    return images_array, labels #Returning array of images and labels list

Building the DNN Model¶

In [11]:
num_classes=one_hot_labels.shape[1] #Number of unique labels

model1=Sequential([
    Flatten(input_shape=(224,224,3)),  #Buildling the model
    Dense(512),
    BatchNormalization(),
    LeakyReLU(alpha=0.1),
    Dropout(0.5),
    
    Dense(256),
    BatchNormalization(),
    LeakyReLU(alpha=0.1),
    Dropout(0.5),
    
    Dense(128),
    BatchNormalization(),
    LeakyReLU(alpha=0.1),
    Dropout(0.5),
    
    Dense(num_classes, activation='softmax')
]) 
 
model1.compile(optimizer=Adam(),loss='categorical_crossentropy',metrics=['accuracy']) #compiling the model

history1=model1.fit(images_array,one_hot_labels,epochs=10,batch_size=32,validation_data=(X_val,y_val)) #fitting the model

In [41]:
fpr = dict()
tpr = dict()
roc_auc_scores = dict()  

for i in range(num_classes):
    fpr[i], tpr[i], _ = roc_curve(y_true == i, y_pred[:, i])
    roc_auc_scores[i] = auc(fpr[i], tpr[i])  


plt.figure(figsize=(10, 8)) #ROC curve
for i in range(num_classes):
    plt.plot(fpr[i], tpr[i], label=f'Class {i} (AUC = {roc_auc_scores[i]:.2f})')

plt.plot([0, 1], [0, 1], 'k--')
plt.title('Receiver Operating Characteristic (ROC) Curve')
plt.xlabel('False Positive Rate')
plt.ylabel('True Positive Rate')
plt.legend(loc="lower right")
plt.show()

Model Interpretation with LIME¶

In [65]:
explainer = lime_image.LimeImageExplainer()
test_image = X_test[0].astype('double')  

explanation = explainer.explain_instance(
    test_image,
    model1.predict,  
    top_labels=5,  
    hide_color=0,  
    num_samples=1000  
)


temp, mask = explanation.get_image_and_mask(
    label=explanation.top_labels[0],  
    positive_only=False,  
    num_features=10,  
    hide_rest=False  
)

plt.figure(figsize=(8, 8))
plt.imshow(mark_boundaries(test_image, mask))
plt.title(f'Explanation for class {explanation.top_labels[0]}')
plt.show()
